<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-12T08:43:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-12T08:43:00-05:00" n="702" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7241</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-12T13:00:00-00:43">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Have been informed that all the German women in Liberia embarked last
                                night on board Spanish vessel under safe-conduct from British Consul
                                General for Germany with the proviso that the vessel must call at
                                Gibraltar for search of their effects before <pb facs="0664" n="492" xml:id="pg_492"/> touching at any point in Spain. Former German
                                Receiver, Customs, following example previously set by former German
                                Consul, sailed on the aforementioned Spanish vessel in violation of
                                the terms of the safe-conduct granted him.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>